 ** PROGRAM 1 : 1. Basic Programs in Data Types **

**Aim:**
To understand and demonstrate the use of basic data types in C.


**Algorithm:**
• Start the program.
• Declare variables of different data types.
• Display values using printf().
• Stop the program.



**Program:**
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
 int a = 10; float b = 5.5; char c = 'A'; double d = 123.456789;
 printf("Integer: %d\n", a);
 printf("Float: %.2f\n", b);
 printf("Character: %c\n", c);
 printf("Double: %.3lf\n", d);
 return 0;
}


**Output :**
Integer: 10
Float: 5.50
Character: A
Double: 123.457


**Result :**

Integer prints as 10

Float prints with 2 decimal places: 5.50

Character prints as A

Double prints with 3 decimal places: 123.457
